#. Tag: date
#: index.docbook:20
#, no-c-format
msgid "2016-06-23"
msgstr "2016-06-23"

#. Tag: releaseinfo
#: index.docbook:21
#, no-c-format
msgid "Plasma 5.8"
msgstr "Plasma 5.8"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:23 index.docbook:37
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Here you can customize window settings specifically only for some windows."
msgstr ""
"Desde aquí podrá personalizar las preferencias para algunas ventanas "
"específicas."

#. Tag: keyword
#: index.docbook:27
#, no-c-format
msgid "<keyword>KDE</keyword>"
msgstr "<keyword>KDE</keyword>"

#. Tag: keyword
#: index.docbook:28
#, no-c-format
msgid "KControl"
msgstr "KControl"

#. Tag: keyword
#: index.docbook:29
#, no-c-format
msgid "window settings"
msgstr "Preferncias de la ventana"

#. Tag: keyword
#: index.docbook:30
#, no-c-format
msgid "window placement"
msgstr "ubicación de la ventana"

#. Tag: keyword
#: index.docbook:31
#, no-c-format
msgid "window size"
msgstr "tamaño de la ventana"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:35
#, no-c-format
msgid "Window Specific Settings: Quick Start"
msgstr "Preferencias específicas de la ventana: inicio rápido"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:41
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Please note that this configuration will not take effect if you do not use "
"&kwin; as your window manager. If you do use a different window manager, "
"please refer to its documentation for how to customize window behavior."
msgstr ""
"Por favor tenga en cuenta que la configuración de este módulo no tendrá "
"efecto si no utiliza &kwin; como administrador de ventanas. Si usa un "
"administrador de ventanas diferente, por favor consulte su documentación "
"para personalizar el comportamiento de las ventanas."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:47
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Many of the settings you can configure here are those you can configure on a "
"global basis in the <guilabel>Window Behavior</guilabel> &systemsettings; "
"module, however some of them are even more detailed."
msgstr ""
"Algunas de las configuraciones que puede modificar aquí son aquellas que se "
"encuentran en la base del <guilabel>Comportamiento de las ventanas</"
"guilabel> del módulo &systemsettings;, sin embargo algunas de ellas están "
"incluso más detalladas."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:51
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"They encompass geometry, placement, whether a window should be kept above or "
"below others, focus stealing prevention, and translucency settings."
msgstr ""
"Están relacionadas con la configuración de la geometría, emplazamiento, "
"cuándo la ventana debe estar sobre o bajo las otras, evitar el robo del foco "
"y transparencia."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:55
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can access this module in two ways: from the titlebar of the application "
"you wish to configure, or from the &systemsettings;. If you start it from "
"within &systemsettings; you can use the <guibutton>New...</guibutton> to "
"create a window profile, and the <guibutton>Detect Window Properties</"
"guibutton> button on the resulting dialog to partially fill in the required "
"information for the application you wish to configure."
msgstr ""
"Puede acceder a este módulo de dos formas: desde la barra de título de la "
"aplicación que desee configurar, o desde &systemsettings;. Si lo inicia "
"desde &systemsettings; puede utilizar <guibutton>Nuevo…</guibutton> para "
"crear un perfil de la ventana, y el botón <guibutton>Detectar</guibutton> en "
"el diálogo resultante para rellenar parcialmente la información requerida "
"por la aplicación que desea configurar."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:63
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can also at any time <guibutton>Modify...</guibutton> or "
"<guibutton>Delete</guibutton> any stored settings profile, and reorder the "
"list. Reordering the list using the <guibutton>Move Up</guibutton> and "
"<guibutton>Move Down</guibutton> buttons effects on how they are applied."
msgstr ""
"También puede <guibutton>Modificar…</guibutton> o <guibutton>Borrar</"
"guibutton> cualquier perfil guardado y reordenar la lista. El orden de la "
"lista (use los botones <guibutton>Subir</guibutton> y <guibutton>Bajar</"
"guibutton>) tiene efecto sobre cómo se aplican."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:72
#, no-c-format
msgid "Overview"
msgstr "Resumen"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:73
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kwin; allows the end-user to define rules to alter an application's window "
"attributes."
msgstr ""
"&kwin; permite al usuario final definir reglas para modificar los atributos "
"de la ventana de una aplicación."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:75
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For example, when an application is started, it can be forced to always run "
"on <emphasis>Virtual Desktop 2</emphasis>. Or a defect in an application can "
"be worked-around to force the window above others."
msgstr ""
"Por ejemplo, cuando se inicia una aplicación, se puede obligar a ejecutarla "
"siempre en el <emphasis>Escritorio virtual 2</emphasis>. O se puede "
"solucionar un defecto de una aplicación para forzar que la ventana se "
"muestre encima de las demás."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:77
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Step-by-step <link linkend=\"examples\">examples</link> are provided along "
"with detailed information on using the <link linkend=\"kwin-rule-editor"
"\">&kwin; Rule Editor</link> to specify <link linkend=\"window-matching"
"\">Window Matching</link> and <link linkend=\"window-attributes\">Window "
"Attributes</link>."
msgstr ""
"Se proporcionan <link linkend=\"examples\">ejemplos</link> paso a paso junto "
"a información detallada sobre el uso del <link linkend=\"kwin-rule-editor"
"\">Editor de reglas de &kwin;</link> para especificar la <link linkend="
"\"window-matching\">Coincidencia de la ventana</link> y los <link linkend="
"\"window-attributes\">Atributos de la ventana</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:80
#, no-c-format
msgid "Examples and Application Workaround"
msgstr "Ejemplos y solución alternativa para la aplicación"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:81
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To see what's possible, detailed <link linkend=\"examples\">examples</link> "
"are provided which can also be used to model your own rules."
msgstr ""
"Para mostrarle lo que se puede hacer, se proporcionan <link linkend="
"\"examples\">ejemplos</link> que también puede usar para dar forma a sus "
"propias reglas."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:83
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A special page is to dedicated to address <link linkend=\"application-"
"workarounds\">Application Workaround</link>."
msgstr ""
"Se dedica una página especial a las <link linkend=\"application-workarounds"
"\">Soluciones alternativas de las aplicaciones</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:86
#, no-c-format
msgid "KWin Rule Editor"
msgstr "Editor de reglas de KWin"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:87
#, no-c-format
msgid "Invoking the KWin Rule Editor"
msgstr "Llamar al editor de reglas de KWin"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:101
#, no-c-format
msgid "There are several ways to invoke the &kwin; Rule Editor. Below are two:"
msgstr ""
"Existen varias formas de mostrar el editor de reglas de &kwin;. A "
"continuación se muestran dos de ellas:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:104
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Right-click on the title-bar of any window, choose <menuchoice><guimenu>More "
"Actions</guimenu><guimenuitem>Window Manager Settings...</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice> and in the <guilabel>Configure</guilabel> window, select "
"<guilabel>Window Rules</guilabel> or"
msgstr ""
"Haga clic derecho sobre la barra de título de una ventana, elija la opción "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Más acciones</guimenu><guimenuitem>Preferencias del "
"gestor de ventanas…</guimenuitem></menuchoice> y, en la ventana "
"<guilabel>Configurar</guilabel>, seleccione <guilabel>Reglas de las "
"ventanas</guilabel> o"

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:107
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenu>System Settings</guimenu><guisubmenu>Window Behavior</"
"guisubmenu><guimenuitem>Window Rules</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<guimenu>Preferencias del sistema</guimenu><guisubmenu>Comportamiento de las "
"ventanas</guisubmenu><guimenuitem>Reglas de las ventanas</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:109
#, no-c-format
msgid "The main window is used to:"
msgstr "La ventana principal se usa para:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:112
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Affect rules with <guilabel>New...</guilabel>, <guilabel>Modify...</"
"guilabel> and <guilabel>Delete</guilabel>"
msgstr ""
"Afectar reglas con <guilabel>Nueva…</guilabel>, <guilabel>Modificar…</"
"guilabel> y <guilabel>Borrar</guilabel>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:113
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Share rules with others via <guilabel>Import</guilabel> and "
"<guilabel>Export</guilabel>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:114
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Ensure desired <link linkend=\"rule-evaluation\">rule evaluation</link> "
"using <guilabel>Move Up</guilabel> and <guilabel>Move Down</guilabel>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:116
#, no-c-format
msgid "Rule Evaluation"
msgstr "Evaluación de reglas"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:117
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When an application starts (or the rules are modified), &kwin; evaluates the "
"rules from the top of the list to the bottom. For all rules which match a "
"window, the collective set of attributes are applied to the window, then the "
"window is displayed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:119
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Should two or more matching rules enable the same attribute, the setting in "
"the <emphasis>first</emphasis> rule in the list is used."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:121
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can tailor children windows for the application by placing the more "
"restrictive rules first - see the <link linkend=\"application-on-all-"
"desktops-and-handle-one-child-window-uniquely\">Kopete and Kopete Chat "
"Window</link> example."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:125
#, no-c-format
msgid "Rule Editor"
msgstr "Editor de reglas"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:139
#, no-c-format
msgid "The editor is composed of four tabs:"
msgstr "El editor se compone de cuatro pestañas:"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:142
#, no-c-format
msgid "Window matching"
msgstr "Coincidencia de ventana"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:143 index.docbook:256
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guilabel>Size &amp; Position</guilabel>"
msgstr "<guilabel>Tamaño y posición</guilabel>"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:144 index.docbook:257
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guilabel>Arrangement &amp; Access</guilabel>"
msgstr "<guilabel>Disposición y acceso</guilabel>"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:145 index.docbook:258
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guilabel>Appearance &amp; Fixes</guilabel>"
msgstr "<guilabel>Apariencia y correcciones</guilabel>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:147
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As the name implies, <guilabel>Window matching</guilabel> is used to specify "
"criteria to match one or more windows. The other three tabs are used to "
"alter the attributes of the matching windows."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:149
#, no-c-format
msgid "Panels can also be affected."
msgstr "Los paneles también se pueden ver afectados."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:151 index.docbook:162
#, no-c-format
msgid "Window Matching"
msgstr "Coincidencia de ventanas"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:152
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each window rule has user specified <link linkend=\"window-matching\">Window "
"Matching</link> criteria. &kwin; uses the criteria to determine whether the "
"rule is applicable for an application."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:155 index.docbook:239
#, no-c-format
msgid "Window Attributes"
msgstr "Atributos de las ventanas"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:156
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Along with Window Matching criteria, each window rule has a set of <link "
"linkend=\"window-attributes\">Window Attributes</link>. The attributes "
"override the corresponding application's settings and are applied before the "
"window is displayed by &kwin;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:176
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <guilabel>Window Matching</guilabel> tab is used to specify the criteria "
"&kwin; uses to evaluate whether the rule is applicable for a given window."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:178
#, no-c-format
msgid "Zero (match any window) or more of the following may be specified:"
msgstr ""
"Se puede indicar cero (coincidir con cualquier ventana) o más de lo "
"siguiente:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:181
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guilabel>Window class (application)</guilabel> - match the class."
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Clase de la ventana (aplicación)</guilabel>: coincidir con la "
"clase."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:182
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Match whole window class</guilabel> - include matching the "
"secondary class."
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Coincidencia completa de la clase de la ventana</guilabel>: "
"incluir que coincida la clase secundaria."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:185
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Window role</guilabel> - restrict the match to the function of the "
"window (&eg; a <emphasis>main window</emphasis>, a <emphasis>chat window</"
"emphasis>, &etc;)"
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Papel de la ventana</guilabel>: restringir la coincidencia a la "
"función de la ventana (por ejemplo, una <emphasis>ventana principal</"
"emphasis>, una <emphasis>ventana de charla</emphasis>, &etc;)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:186
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Window types</guilabel> - restrict the match to the type of "
"window: <guilabel>Normal Window</guilabel>, <guilabel>Dialog Window</"
"guilabel>, &etc;"
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Tipos de ventanas</guilabel>: restringir la coincidencia al tipo "
"de la ventana (por ejemplo, <guilabel>Ventana normal</guilabel>, "
"<guilabel>Ventana de diálogo</guilabel>, &etc;)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:187
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Window title</guilabel> - restrict the match to the title of the "
"window."
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Título de la ventana</guilabel>: restringir la coincidencia al "
"título de la ventana."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:188
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Machine (hostname)</guilabel> - restrict the match to the host "
"name associated with the window."
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Máquina (nombre de la máquina)</guilabel>: restringir la "
"coincidencia al nombre de la máquina asociada con la ventana."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:190
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"While it's possible to manually enter the above information, the preferred "
"method is to use the <guilabel>Detect Window Properties</guilabel> button."
msgstr ""
"Aunque es posible introducir manualmente la información anterior, el método "
"preferido es usar el botón <guilabel>Detectar las propiedades de la ventana</"
"guilabel>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:192
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For each field, the following operators can be applied against the field "
"value:"
msgstr "Puede aplicar los siguientes operadores sobre el valor de cada campo:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:195
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guilabel>Unimportant</guilabel> - ignore the field."
msgstr "<guilabel>Sin importancia</guilabel> - ignorar el campo."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:196
#, no-c-format
msgid "Exact Match"
msgstr "Coincidencia exacta"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:197
#, no-c-format
msgid "Substring Match"
msgstr "Coincidencia de subcadena de texto"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:199
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Both <guilabel>Exact Match</guilabel> and <guilabel>Substring Match</"
"guilabel> implement case insensitive matching. For example, <emphasis>AB</"
"emphasis> matches the string <emphasis>AB</emphasis>, <emphasis>ab</"
"emphasis>, <emphasis>Ab</emphasis> and <emphasis>aB</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"Tanto <guilabel>Coincidencia exacta</guilabel> como <guilabel>Coincidencia "
"de subcadena de texto</guilabel> implementan coincidencia sin distinguir "
"entre mayúsculas y minúsculas. Por ejemplo, <emphasis>AB</emphasis> coincide "
"con la cadenas <emphasis>AB</emphasis>, <emphasis>ab</emphasis>, "
"<emphasis>Ab</emphasis> y <emphasis>aB</emphasis>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:202
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Regular Expression</guilabel> - Qt's regular expressions are "
"implemented - see <ulink url=\"https://doc.qt.io/qt-5/qregexp.html\">pattern "
"matching using regular expressions</ulink>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:204
#, no-c-format
msgid "Detect Window Properties"
msgstr "Detectar las propiedades de la ventana"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:218
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <guilabel>Detect Window Properties</guilabel> function simplifies the "
"process of entering the matching-criteria."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:221
#, no-c-format
msgid "For the application you'd like to create a rule, start the application."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:222
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Next, in the <guilabel>Window matching</guilabel> tab, set the number of "
"seconds of delay before the <guilabel>Detect Window Properties</guilabel> "
"function starts. The default is zero seconds."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:223
#, no-c-format
msgid "Click on <guilabel>Detect Window Properties</guilabel> and"
msgstr "Pulse en <guilabel>Detectar las propiedades de la ventana</guilabel> y"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:224
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When the mouse-cursor turns to cross-hairs, place it inside the application "
"window (not the title bar) and left-click."
msgstr ""
"Cuando el cursor del ratón cambie a una cruceta, sitúelo dentro de la "
"ventana de la aplicación (no en su barra de título) y haga un clic izquierdo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:225
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A new window is presented with information about the selected window. Select "
"the desired fields:"
msgstr ""
"Se muestra una ventana con información sobre la ventana que ha seleccionado. "
"Seleccione los campos que desee:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:226
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Secondary class name</guilabel> - some applications have a "
"secondary class name. This value can be used to restrict windows by this "
"value."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:227
#, no-c-format
msgid "Window role"
msgstr "Papel de la ventana"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:228
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guilabel>Window type</guilabel>"
msgstr "<guilabel>Tipo de ventana</guilabel>"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:229
#, no-c-format
msgid "Window title"
msgstr "Título de la ventana"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:233
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Click the <guilabel>OK</guilabel> button to back-fill the <guilabel>Window "
"Matching</guilabel> criteria."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:235
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By using a combination of the information, a rule can apply to an entire "
"application (by <guilabel>Class</guilabel>) or a to a specific window "
"<guilabel>Type</guilabel> within the <guilabel>Class</guilabel> - say a "
"<guilabel>Toolbar</guilabel>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:253
#, no-c-format
msgid "The attributes which can be set are grouped by function in three tabs:"
msgstr ""
"Los atributos que se pueden definir están agrupados por su función en tres "
"pestañas:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:260
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each attribute has a set of parameters which determines its disposition."
msgstr ""
"Cada atributo tiene un conjunto de parámetros que determina su disposición."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:262
#, no-c-format
msgid "Parameters"
msgstr "Parámetros"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:263
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each attribute, minimally, accepts one of the following parameters. "
"Additional, attribute-specific arguments are listed within each <link "
"linkend=\"attributes\">attribute</link> definition."
msgstr ""
"Cada atributo, mínimamente, acepta uno de los siguientes parámetros. Los "
"argumentos adicionales específicos de los atributos se enumeran dentro de "
"cada definición de <link linkend=\"attributes\">atributo</link>."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:266
#, no-c-format
msgid "Do Not Affect"
msgstr "No afectar"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:268
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Ensure a subsequent rule, which matches the window, does not affect the "
"attribute."
msgstr ""
"Asegurar que una regla posterior, que coincida con la ventana, no afecte el "
"atributo."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:271
#, no-c-format
msgid "Apply Initially"
msgstr "Aplicar inicialmente"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:273
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Start the window with the attribute and allow it to be changed at run-time."
msgstr ""
"Iniciar la ventana con el atributo y permitirle que se pueda cambiar en "
"tiempo de ejecución."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:276
#, no-c-format
msgid "Remember"
msgstr "Recordar"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:278
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the attribute setting as defined in the rule and if changed at run-time, "
"save and use the new value instead."
msgstr ""
"Usar el ajuste del atributo como se define en la regla y, si se cambia en "
"tiempo de ejecución, guardar y usar el nuevo valor en su lugar."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:281
#, no-c-format
msgid "Force"
msgstr "Forzar"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:283
#, no-c-format
msgid "The setting cannot be changed at run-time."
msgstr "El ajuste no se puede cambiar en tiempo de ejecución."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:286
#, no-c-format
msgid "Apply Now, Force Temporarily"
msgstr "Aplicar ahora, forzar temporalmente"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:288
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Apply/Force the setting once and unset the attribute.The difference between "
"the two is at run-time, <guilabel>Apply Now</guilabel> allows the attribute "
"to be changed and <guilabel>Force Temporarily</guilabel> prohibits it to be "
"altered until all affected windows exit."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:292
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For <guilabel>Apply Now</guilabel>, if the rule has no other attributes set, "
"the rule is deleted after evaluation whereas <guilabel>Force Temporarily</"
"guilabel>, the rule is deleted after the last affected window terminates."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:295
#, no-c-format
msgid "Attributes"
msgstr "Atributos"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:296
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <guilabel>Detect Window Properties</guilabel> button back-fills "
"attribute-specific values - for more information see <link linkend=\"window-"
"matching\">Window Matching</link>. For example the height and width values "
"of the <guilabel>Size</guilabel> attribute is set to the height and width of "
"the detected window."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:298
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Yes/No</guilabel> arguments are used to toggle on or off "
"attributes. Leniency with grammar helps one understand how a setting will be "
"processed. <inlinemediaobject> <imageobject> <imagedata fileref=\"Face-smile."
"png\" format=\"PNG\"/> </imageobject> </inlinemediaobject> For example, the "
"attribute <guilabel>Skip taskbar</guilabel>, when set to <guilabel>No</"
"guilabel> means do not skip the taskbar. In other words, show the window in "
"the taskbar."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:300
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Size &amp; Position</title>"
msgstr "<title>Tamaño y posición</title>"

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:302
#, no-c-format
msgid "Position"
msgstr "Posición"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:304
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Position the window's upper left corner at the specified x,y coordinate."
msgstr ""
"Situar la esquina superior izquierda de la ventana en las coordenadas x,y "
"indicadas."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:308
#, no-c-format
msgid "&kwin;'s origin, (0,0), is the upper left of the desktop."
msgstr ""
"El origen de &kwin;, (0,0), es la parte superior izquierda del escritorio."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:311
#, no-c-format
msgid "Size"
msgstr "Tamaño"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:313
#, no-c-format
msgid "The width and height of the window."
msgstr "La anchura y la altura de la ventana."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:316
#, no-c-format
msgid "Maximized horizontally, Maximized vertically"
msgstr "Maximizada horizontalmente, maximizada verticalmente"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:318
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These attributes are used to toggle the maximum horizontal/minimum "
"horizontal window attribute."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:321
#, no-c-format
msgid "Desktop, Activity, Screen"
msgstr "Escritorio, Actividad, Pantalla"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:323
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Place the window on the specified <emphasis>(Virtual) Desktop</emphasis>, "
"<emphasis>Activity</emphasis> or <emphasis>Screen</emphasis>. Use "
"<guilabel>All Desktops</guilabel> to place the window on all "
"<emphasis>Virtual Desktops</emphasis>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:326
#, no-c-format
msgid "Fullscreen, Minimized, Shaded"
msgstr "Pantalla completa, minimizada, recogida"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:328
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Toggle the Fullscreen, Minimize and Shading window attribute. For example, a "
"window can be started Minimized or if it is started Minimized, it can be "
"forced to not."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:332
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Maximized attribute is emulated by using both <guilabel>Maximized "
"horizontally</guilabel> and <guilabel>Maximized vertically</guilabel> or "
"<guilabel>Initial placement</guilabel> with the <guilabel>Maximizing</"
"guilabel> argument."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:335
#, no-c-format
msgid "Initial placement"
msgstr "Colocación inicial"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:337
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Override the global window placement strategy with one of the following:"
msgstr ""
"Anular la estrategia global de ubicación de ventanas con una de las "
"siguientes opciones:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:339
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Default</guilabel> - use the global window placement strategy."
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Predeterminada</guilabel>: usar la estrategia global de ubicación "
"de ventanas."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:340
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guilabel>No Placement</guilabel> - top-left corner."
msgstr "<guilabel>Sin ubicación</guilabel>: esquina superior izquierda."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:341
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Minimal Overlapping</guilabel> - place where no other window "
"exists."
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Solapamiento mínimo</guilabel>: situar donde no haya ninguna "
"ventana."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:342
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guilabel>Maximized</guilabel> - start the window maximized."
msgstr "<guilabel>Maximizada</guilabel>: iniciar la ventana maximizada."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:343
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guilabel>Centered</guilabel> - center of the desktop."
msgstr "<guilabel>Centrada</guilabel>: centro del escritorio."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:344
#, no-c-format
msgid "Random"
msgstr "Aleatoria"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:345
#, no-c-format
msgid "In Top-Left Corner"
msgstr "En la esquina superior izquierda"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:346
#, no-c-format
msgid "Under Mouse"
msgstr "Bajo el ratón"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:347
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>On Main Window</guilabel> - restrict placement of a child window "
"to the boundaries of the parent window."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:352
#, no-c-format
msgid "Ignore requested geometry"
msgstr "Ignorar la geometría solicitada"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:354
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Toggle whether to accept or ignore the window's requested geometry position. "
"To avoid conflicts between the default placement strategy and the window's "
"request, the placement strategy is ignored when the window's request is "
"accepted."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:357
#, no-c-format
msgid "Minimum size, Maximum size"
msgstr "Tamaño mínimo, Tamaño máximo"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:359
#, no-c-format
msgid "The minimum and maximum size allowed for the window."
msgstr "El tamaño mínimo y máximo permitido para la ventana."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:362
#, no-c-format
msgid "Obey geometry restrictions"
msgstr "Obedecer restricciones de geometría"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:364
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Toggle whether to adhere to the window's requested aspect ratio or "
"<emphasis>base increment</emphasis>.In order to understand this attribute, "
"some background is required. Briefly, windows must request from the Window "
"Manager, a base increment: the minimum number of <emphasis>height</emphasis> "
"X <emphasis>width</emphasis> pixels per re-size request. Typically, it's "
"1x1. Other windows though, for example terminal emulators or editors, use "
"fixed-fonts and request their base-increment according to the size of one "
"character."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:369
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Arrangement &amp; Access</title>"
msgstr "<title>Disposición y acceso</title>"

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:371
#, no-c-format
msgid "Keep above, Keep below"
msgstr "Mantener encima, Mantener debajo"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:373
#, no-c-format
msgid "Toggle whether to keep the window above/below all others."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:376
#, no-c-format
msgid "Autogroup with identical"
msgstr "Agrupar automáticamente con idénticas"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:378
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Toggle the grouping (commonly known as <emphasis>tabbing</emphasis>) of "
"windows."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:381
#, no-c-format
msgid "Autogroup in foreground"
msgstr "Agrupar automáticamente en primer plano"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:383
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Toggle whether to make the window active when it is added to the current "
"Autogroup."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:386
#, no-c-format
msgid "Autogroup by ID"
msgstr "Agrupar automáticamente por ID"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:388
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Create a group via a user-defined ID. More than one rule can share the same "
"ID to allow for seemingly unrelated windows to be grouped."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:392
#, no-c-format
msgid "Skip taskbar"
msgstr "Omitir la barra de tareas"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:394
#, no-c-format
msgid "Toggle whether to display the window in the taskbar."
msgstr "Controla si se debe mostrar la ventana en la barra de tareas."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:397
#, no-c-format
msgid "Skip pager"
msgstr "Omitir el paginador"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:399
#, no-c-format
msgid "Toggle whether to display the window in pager."
msgstr "Controla si se debe mostrar la ventana en el paginador."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:417
#, no-c-format
msgid "Skip switcher"
msgstr "Omitir el cambiador"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:419
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Toggle whether to display the window in the <guilabel>ALT+TAB</guilabel> "
"list."
msgstr ""
"Controla si se debe mostrar la ventana en la lista de <guilabel>Alt+Tab</"
"guilabel>."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:422
#, no-c-format
msgid "Shortcut"
msgstr "Atajo de teclado"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:424
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Assign a shortcut to the window. When <guilabel>Edit...</guilabel> is "
"clicked, additional instructions are presented."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:429
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Appearance &amp; Fixes</title>"
msgstr "<title>Apariencia y correcciones</title>"

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:431
#, no-c-format
msgid "No titlebar and frame"
msgstr "Sin barra de título ni marco"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:433
#, no-c-format
msgid "Toggle whether to display the titlebar and frame around the window."
msgstr ""
"Controla si se debe mostrar la barra de título y el marco alrededor de la "
"ventana."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:436
#, no-c-format
msgid "Titlebar color scheme"
msgstr "Esquema de color de la barra de título"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:438
#, no-c-format
msgid "Select a color scheme for the titlebar of the window."
msgstr "Seleccionar un esquema de color para la barra de título de la ventana."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:441
#, no-c-format
msgid "Active/Inactive opacity"
msgstr "Opacidad activa/inactiva"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:443
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When the window is active/inactive, set its opacity to the percentage "
"specified."
msgstr ""
"Cuando la ventana está activa/inactiva, define su opacidad al porcentaje "
"indicado."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:447
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Active/Inactive opacity</guilabel> can only be affected when "
"<guilabel>Desktop Effects</guilabel> are enabled."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:450
#, no-c-format
msgid "Focus stealing prevention"
msgstr "Prevención de la captura del foco"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:452
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When a window wants focus, control on a scale (from <guilabel>None</"
"guilabel> to <guilabel>Extreme</guilabel>) whether to honor the request and "
"place above all other windows, or ignore its request (potentially leaving "
"the window behind other windows):"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:454
#, no-c-format
msgid "None - Always grant focus to the window."
msgstr "Ninguna - Siempre garantiza el foco a la ventana."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:455
#, no-c-format
msgid "<para>Low</para>"
msgstr "<para>Baja</para>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:456
#, no-c-format
msgid "Normal"
msgstr "Normal"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:457
#, no-c-format
msgid "High"
msgstr "Alta"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:458
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Extreme - The window's focus request is denied. Focus is only granted by "
"explicitly requesting via the mousing."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:464
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"See <guilabel>Accept focus</guilabel> to make a window read-only - not "
"accept any keyboard input."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:467
#, no-c-format
msgid "Accept focus"
msgstr "Aceptar el foco"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:469
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Toggle whether the window accepts keyboard input. Make the window read-only."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:472
#, no-c-format
msgid "Ignore global shortcuts"
msgstr "Ignorar atajos de teclado globales"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:474
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Toggle whether to ignore global shortcuts (as defined by "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>System Settings</guimenu><guisubmenu>Shortcuts and "
"Gestures</guisubmenu><guimenuitem>Global Shortcuts</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice> or by running <varname>kcmshell6 keys</varname> in "
"<guilabel>konsole</guilabel>) while the window is active."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:477
#, no-c-format
msgid "Closeable"
msgstr "Se puede cerrar"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:479
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Toggle whether to display the <guilabel>Close</guilabel> button on the title "
"bar."
msgstr ""
"Controla si se debe mostrar el botón <guilabel>Cerrar</guilabel> en la barra "
"de título."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:483
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A terminal window may still be closed by the end user by ending the shell "
"session however using <guilabel>Accept focus</guilabel> to disable keyboard "
"input will make it more difficult to close the window."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:486
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis role=\"bold\">Window type</emphasis>"
msgstr "<emphasis role=\"bold\">Tipo de ventana</emphasis>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:488
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Change the window to another type and inherit the characteristics of that "
"window:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:490
#, no-c-format
msgid "Normal Window"
msgstr "Ventana normal"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:491
#, no-c-format
msgid "Dialog Window"
msgstr "Ventana de diálogo"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:492
#, no-c-format
msgid "Utility Window"
msgstr "Ventana de utilidad"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:493
#, no-c-format
msgid "Dock (panel)"
msgstr "Panel"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:494
#, no-c-format
msgid "Toolbar"
msgstr "Barra de herramientas"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:495
#, no-c-format
msgid "Torn-Off Menu"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:496
#, no-c-format
msgid "Splash Screen"
msgstr "Pantalla de bienvenida"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:497
#, no-c-format
msgid "Desktop"
msgstr "Escritorio"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:498
#, no-c-format
msgid "Standalone Menubar"
msgstr "Barra de menú autónoma"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:499
#, no-c-format
msgid "On Screen Display"
msgstr "Visualización en pantalla"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:505
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use with care because unwanted results may be introduced. For example, a "
"<guilabel>Splash Screen</guilabel> is a automatically closed by &kwin; when "
"clicked."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:508
#, no-c-format
msgid "Block compositing"
msgstr "Bloquear la composición"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:510
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Toggle whether to disable compositing while the window <emphasis>exists</"
"emphasis>. If compositing is enabled and the rule specifies to disable "
"compositing, while <emphasis>any</emphasis> matching window exists, "
"compositing will be disabled. Compositing is re-enabled when the last "
"matching window terminates."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:517
#, no-c-format
msgid "Examples"
msgstr "Ejemplos"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:518
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The first example details all the necessary steps to create the rules. In "
"order to keep this page a manageable size, subsequent examples only list "
"steps specific to the example."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:520
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <guilabel>Pager</guilabel> attribute refers to the <guilabel>Virtual "
"Desktop Manager</guilabel>:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:533
#, no-c-format
msgid "Pin a Window to a Desktop and set other Attributes"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:534
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Pin &akregator; to <emphasis>Virtual Desktop 2</emphasis>. Additionally, "
"start the application with a preferred size and position. For each "
"attribute, use the <guilabel>Apply Initially</guilabel> <link linkend="
"\"parameters\">parameter</link> so it can be overridden at run-time."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:536
#, no-c-format
msgid "The &kwin; rule is created as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:539
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Start &akregator; on <emphasis>desktop two</emphasis>, size and position it "
"to suit:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:551
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Right-click on the titlebar and select <menuchoice><guimenu>More Actions</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Window Manager Settings...</guimenuitem></menuchoice>:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:563
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select the <guilabel>Window Rules</guilabel> in the left column and click on "
"<guilabel>New...</guilabel>:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:575
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <guilabel>Edit Window-Specific Settings</guilabel> window is displayed. "
"<guilabel>Window matching</guilabel> is the default tab:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:587
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Click <guilabel>Detect Window Properties</guilabel> with <guilabel>0s delay</"
"guilabel> the cursor immediately turns into cross-hairs. Click (anywhere) "
"inside the &akregator; window (but not the title bar). The window criteria "
"are presented. Match only by primary class name so leave the check boxes "
"unchecked - for additional information see <link linkend=\"window-matching"
"\">window matching</link>:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:599
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Clicking <guilabel>OK</guilabel> the previous window back-fills the results "
"in the <guilabel>Window Matching</guilabel> tab. Enter a meaningful text in "
"the <guilabel>Description</guilabel> field (which is displayed in the "
"<guilabel>KWin Rule</guilabel> window):"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:611
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Enable the window attributes: <guilabel>Position</guilabel>, <guilabel>Size</"
"guilabel> and <guilabel>Desktop</guilabel>. The initial values are set by "
"<guilabel>Detect Window Properties</guilabel> and can be overridden:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:623
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Clicking <guilabel>OK</guilabel> in the previous window returns to the main "
"<guilabel>KWin Rules</guilabel>. The new rule with its description is listed:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:635
#, no-c-format
msgid "Click <guilabel>OK</guilabel> to close the window."
msgstr "Pulse <guilabel>Aceptar</guilabel> para cerrar la ventana."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:636
#, no-c-format
msgid "Done."
msgstr "Terminado."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:639
#, no-c-format
msgid "Application on all Desktops and Handle One Child Window Uniquely"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:640
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Except for conversation windows, display &kopete; and its children windows "
"on all desktops and skip the systray and pager. For children conversation "
"windows, treat them as the parent window except show them in systray."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:642
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For each attribute, use the <guilabel>Force</guilabel> <link linkend="
"\"parameters\">parameter</link> so it can not be overridden."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:644
#, no-c-format
msgid "In order to implement the above, two rules need to be created:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:647
#, no-c-format
msgid "A rule for <guilabel>Kopete Chat</guilabel> and"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:648
#, no-c-format
msgid "A rule for &kopete;"
msgstr "Una regla para &kopete;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:650
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <guilabel>Kopete Chat</guilabel> rule's matching-criteria is more "
"restrictive than the <emphasis>Kopete</emphasis> rule as it needs to match a "
"specific Window Role: the chat window. Due to <link linkend=\"rule-evaluation"
"\">rule evaluation</link> processing, the <guilabel>Kopete Chat</guilabel> "
"rule must precede the &kopete; rule in the <link linkend=\"kopete-kwin-rule-"
"list\">KWin Rule list for Kopete</link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:652
#, no-c-format
msgid "Kopete Chat Rule"
msgstr "Regla de charla para Kopete"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:653
#, no-c-format
msgid "Assuming a <guilabel>Kopete Chat</guilabel> window is open:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:656
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use <guilabel>Detect Window Properties</guilabel> and select the "
